reviews.review_text: indy university 77 thank you for this wonderful concert from the assembly hall at bloomington,indiana.my deadhead friends Bufue and fig and i had just seen them the night before in Dekalb,Il.northern Ill. university.we saw a great show there and we decided to drive to indy for the show there the next night.we were burned out from the night before.we lost an hour going east into indy and got there just as the concert had started.we got seats to the left side behind the stage and it was like being a part of the band.we were that close to jerry and the rest of the band.believe it or not there was only about half a crowd there,thats why we could almost sit anywhere.this concert is hot.they were right on everything.a cool tennessee jed,a jammin lazy,and then playing in the band and the rest of show just blows you away.WOW.thank you "steve and dave" so much for this great 77 concert.
